1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:06,777
Day 3 I made a decision most people told me was dumb — I gave everything away for free.

2
00:00:06,777 --> 00:00:08,180
I can't code.

3
00:00:08,180 --> 00:00:10,277
9 years in crypto.

4
00:00:10,277 --> 00:00:13,000
AI's trading my thousand dollars.

5
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:14,347
Day 3.

6
00:00:14,347 --> 00:00:20,333
I had a choice that day — turn this into a paid product, or make it a public experiment.

7
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:22,541
I picked the expensive one.

8
00:00:22,541 --> 00:00:24,513
13 lessons, free.

9
00:00:24,513 --> 00:00:26,305
Live balance, free.

10
00:00:26,305 --> 00:00:30,875
Every trade, every win rate, every drawdown — free.

11
00:00:30,875 --> 00:00:37,208
The only thing behind the paywall — the specific parameters that would let a copycat clone the strategy.

12
00:00:37,208 --> 00:00:41,097
A friend asked me — you're burning your own bridge, you know that, right?

13
00:00:41,097 --> 00:00:42,694
I told him no.

14
00:00:42,694 --> 00:00:45,750
This is the only honest promise I can make.

15
00:00:45,750 --> 00:00:50,722
Because if I'm wrong, I want everyone to watch me be wrong in real time.

16
00:00:50,722 --> 00:00:53,319
And if I'm right, same thing.

17
00:00:53,319 --> 00:00:55,580
Want people to trust what you're building?

18
00:00:55,580 --> 00:00:58,069
Let them watch it work for free, first.

19
00:00:58,069 --> 00:01:01,888
Day 4 tomorrow — the bug I almost didn't check.

20
00:01:01,888 --> 00:01:03,319
Follow along.

